<p>Create a View of the Staff table which omits details that should remain private to all other employees other than management and human resources including salary, date of birth and address. Implement the View in MySQL (see View Syntax and Using Views) or use MySQL Workbench if you wish to define the View as an update to DHv1_3.mwb.</p>  <p>The following is the staff table:</p>  <ul> <li>sno: char(5)</li> <li>fname:   varchar(10) NULL</li> <li>lname:   varchar(10) NULL</li> <li>lname:   varchar(10) NULL</li> <li>lname:   varchar(10) NULL</li> <li>address: varchar(35) NULL</li> <li>tel_no:  char(10) NULL   </li> <li>position:    varchar(10) NULL</li> <li>sex: char(1) NULL</li> <li>dob: char(9) NULL</li> <li>salary:  smallint(6) NULL</li> <li>nin: char(10) NULL</li> <li>nin: char(10) NULL</li> <li>Branch_bno:  char(5)</li> </ul>  <p><strong>Question</strong>: Will you please do it for me?</p>